# Shopify Store Configuration
# See docs/DEPLOYMENT.md for full details on the deployment pipeline

# ============================================================================
# STORE URLS
# ============================================================================
# Production: bare-performance-nutrition.myshopify.com
# Staging:    dev-bare-performance-nutrition.myshopify.com
#
# For local development, use the store that matches your workflow:
#   - Use staging store for day-to-day development
#   - Use production store only for production debugging/hotfixes
#
STORE_URL=dev-bare-performance-nutrition.myshopify.com

# ============================================================================
# THEME ID
# ============================================================================
# Which theme should you use for local development?
#
#   Personal dev theme (recommended):
#     Create your own unpublished theme for isolated development.
#     1. Go to Shopify Admin → Online Store → Themes
#     2. Duplicate an existing theme
#     3. Rename it to "Dev - [Your Name]"
#     4. Click ... → Edit code to get the theme ID from the URL
#
#   Staging theme:
#     Use when you need to test alongside recent team changes.
#     (Get this ID from your team or GitHub environment variables)
#
# To find any theme ID:
#   Go to Shopify Admin → Online Store → Themes → ... → Edit code
#   The ID is in the URL: /themes/THEME_ID/editor
#
THEME_ID=

# ============================================================================
# PRODUCTION THEME ID (for settings sync)
# ============================================================================
# Used by `yarn sync:production` to pull settings from the live theme.
# This captures theme editor changes before releases for version control.
#
# Find the production theme ID the same way as above (Edit code → URL).
#
PROD_THEME_ID=
